Date-FromToday

This module is used to calcualte the date so many days in the past/future from
today.  The format of the date can also be specified and month names can be
translated from 01 .. 12 to Jan .. Dec.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Date::FromToday

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Date-FromToday

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Date-FromToday

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Date-FromToday

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Date-FromToday/


